commText: Welcome back! Mumbai are in a team huddle and Nuwan Thushara receives his MI cap from Bumrah. Meanwhile, Hardik gets a special shirt (No. 100) from Lasith Malinga as this is his 100th match for the club. Final inputs from the skipper and off they disperse. Jos Buttler comes in as the Impact Player for RR, he replaces Chahal. For MI, Thushara replaces Suryakumar Yadav. All in readiness. Here's Hardik with a slip in place....
Best figures for RR in IPL 6/14 Sohail Tanvir vs CSK Jaipur 2008 5/16 James Faulkner vs SRH Hyderabad 2013 5/18 Sandeep Sharma vs MI Jaipur 2024 * 5/20 James Faulkner vs SRH Jaipur 2013

Nehal Wadhera: It’s a really good opportunity. Finally it came, I’m happy to do well but I will be more happy if my team wins. We lost of couple of wickets early on, my duty was to wait for the loose balls, we had done it together in the previous season and we had the confidence in ourselves to do well again, hoping our team crosses the line and wins. When we usually have practice sessions, I turn up on the ground early. I used to go early with Surya bhai and we used to play like match simulation, that gave me confidence that although I’m not playing a match, it feels like playing a match in practice. It’s amazing to bat with him, the fun and banter also keeps going in between, the way he (Tilak) batted is also commendable, credit to him.

21:17 Local Time, 15:47 GMT, 21:17 IST: This is the lowest first innings total of the season at this venue! Both teams got what they wanted at the toss. Rohit fell in the first over trying to be aggressive against Boult. Ishan Kishan chased a wide one to nick off. SKY became Sandeep Sharma's second victim and in the process fell to the latter for the fourth time in IPL. While they were reduced to 20/4 in the reverse fixture, MI were 20/3 today. Nabi got a promotion and looked in good touch but he was nipped out by Chahal who in the process became the first IPL player to pick 200 wickets. At 52/4, Mumbai were in a spot of bother; that's when Tilak Varma and Nehal Wadhera joined hands. Not only did the two youngsters stabilise the innings by counterattacking, they also put MI in a very good position (151/4 after 16 overs). Wadhera, playing his first match of the season, fell for 49 and RR came back strongly in the death overs. Last 4 overs: 28 runs | 5 wickets. While Avesh Khan nailed the yorkers in the penultimate power, Sandeep bowled outside the batters' hitting zone to pick up three wickets in the 20th over and claim a fifer in his comeback match.
Sandeep Sharma to Bumrah, 2 runs, 125.3kph, swung away to deep square leg off the inner part of the bat
Jasprit Bumrah, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Sandeep Sharma to Tim David, out Caught by Riyan Parag!! Fifer for Sandeep Sharma! Big smile on his face as he has his arms aloft. 122.8kph, full toss, David stays deep to muscle it over deep midwicket. More height than distance, Parag settles under calmly and pouches it. Tim David c Riyan Parag b Sandeep Sharma 3(5)
Sandeep Sharma to Tim David, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Sandeep Sharma to Tim David, no run, 128.8kph, short ball outside off, David moves across and slams the pull, finds deep mid and turns down the single
Three balls left; what can Tim David do?
Sandeep Sharma to Chawla, 1 run, 122.4kph, full toss outside off, driven down to long-off for a single. No hat-trick for Sandeep
Piyush Chawla, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Sandeep Sharma to Gerald Coetzee, out Caught by Hetmyer!! 124.4kph, scrambled seam length ball outside off, Coetzee decides to loft and gets it off the bottom part of the bat. A straightforward catch to long-on. A wicket and more importantly, Tim David will be off strike. Gerald Coetzee c Hetmyer b Sandeep Sharma 0(1)
Sandeep Sharma to Gerald Coetzee, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Gerald Coetzee, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Sandeep Sharma to Tilak Varma, out Caught by Powell!! 116.4kph, slower ball on a short of length, Tilak Varma waits to heave it away but picks out long-on. Powell comes in, takes the catch and tumbles. End of a superb knock from Varma. Gets a standing ovation from his team-mates in the dug-out. Tilak Varma c Powell b Sandeep Sharma 65(45) [4s-5 6s-3]
Sandeep Sharma to Tilak Varma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Sandeep Sharma [3.0-0-15-2] is back into the attack

Avesh Khan to Tim David, 2 runs, 141.4kph, Khan Avesh misses his yorker by an inch or two and a shuffling David manages to get under it as he drills it to straight long-off. Hetmyer makes a diving stop and throws it to the converging long-on fielder. Brilliant over from Avesh - just 6 off it!
Avesh Khan to Tilak Varma, 1 run, 135.9kph, nails another yorker does Avesh and Tilak Varma toe-ends it to cover
Avesh Khan aborts as Tilak Varma probably wasn't ready. He was seen tapping the bat. The umpire has a word with the batter
Avesh Khan to Tim David, 1 run, 138.4kph, yorker length outside off, a shuffling David drills it to long-on for a single
Avesh Khan to Tim David, wide, 135.3kph, sprays this too wide outside off, left alone. Samson dives to collect it
Avesh Khan to Tim David, no run, 142.7kph, yorker outside off, Tim David squeeze-drives straight to extra cover
Avesh Khan to Tim David, wide, goes for the wide yorker, bowls it well outside off. Tim David moved across but it was too wide
Tim David, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Avesh Khan to Hardik Pandya, out Lbw!! Hardik Pandya adjudged lbw and he reviews. Full toss at 140.4kph, a shuffling Hardik misses the flick to get pinned on the pads adjacent to the stumps. That's crashing into the leg-stump! The onfield call stays. MI burn both their reviews off successive deliveries. Hardik Pandya lbw b Avesh Khan 10(10) [4s-1]
Avesh Khan to Hardik Pandya, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!
Another review!

Avesh Khan to Hardik Pandya, no run, DRS! MI review for a wide. 136.6kph, wide yorker, Hardik Pandya moves across to go over point/cover and loses his shape in the process. No contact. Hardik Pandya had moved across even before the ball was delivered. So, even though the ball was slightly outside the tramline, it won't be a wide call. MI lose a review!
Avesh Khan [3.0-0-43-0] is back into the attack
Two overs to go. 180-190 has been the average score at this venue this season...
Chahal to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, 91.4kph, full delivery, driven hard to long-on
Chahal to Hardik Pandya, 2 runs, 94.6kph, off-stump line, punched to extra cover. A needless throw results in an extra run, courtesy overthrows

Chahal to Hardik Pandya, FOUR, Chahal overpitches around leg and Hardik Pandya clears his front leg to drill it straight down the ground. Hetmyer dives to his left from long-on but fails to stop it. Chahal isn't a happy man
Chahal to Hardik Pandya, no run, 95.9kph, quick ball on a length that skids off the deck around off, cut to backward point
Chahal to Tilak Varma, 1 run, 91.6kph, full outside off, Varma doesn't quite get under it and fails to get the elevation as he looks to loft. Goes to long-off on the bounce
Chahal to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, 88.5kph, driven along the ground to long-off for a single

Boult to Tilak Varma, SIX, the six spoils the over for Boult! 128.7kph, slower ball, full in length, Tilak Varma crouches low and swings hard to flog it over deep midwicket. Boult finishes with 4-0-32-2!
Boult to Tilak Varma, wide, 111.2kph, slower ball bouncer, Tilak Varma tries to go over backward point/short third man. Doesn't connect as it's too high
Boult to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, 121.1kph, slow and short, leg-lined, pulled to deep backward square leg
Boult to Hardik Pandya, no run, 134.7kph, round the wicket, almost in the blockhole and Pandya jams it back to the bowler
Youngest to 1000 IPL runs 20y 218d Rishabh Pant 21y 130d Yashavi Jaiswal 21y 166d Tilak Varma * 21y 169d Prithvi Shaw 21y 183d Sanju Samson
Boult to Tilak Varma, 1 run, 136kph, very full, drilled to long-on and Hetmyer keeps the batters down to one
Boult to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, length ball around off and Hardik Pandya strokes it to deep cover to get off the mark
Hardik Pandya, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Boult to Nehal Wadhera, out Caught by Sandeep Sharma!! Nehal Wadhera missses his fifty by a run but he's played a gem in his first match this season. Much-needed breakthrough for RR and it's Boult who's broken the 99-run stand. 107.8kph, slower ball, short and wide of off, Wadhera spots it and hops and try and upper-cut. However, he fails to generate enough power behind it and it's a dolly for backward point. Nehal Wadhera c Sandeep Sharma b Boult 49(24) [4s-3 6s-4]
Boult to Nehal Wadhera, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Trent Boult [3.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack

Chahal to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, quicker, wider, may have been the googly, Wadhera swings hard and miscues as it comes off the bottom part of the bat. Fortunately for him, it falls short of the forward-running deep cover fielder. 20 runs off the over!

Chahal to Nehal Wadhera, SIX, another six. 92.9kph, Chahal bowls wider but it's a leggie, Wadhera gets close to the pitch of the ball by pressing forward and swings it over long-on. Powell leaps but the ball goes well over him
Chahal to Nehal Wadhera, SIX, 90.8kph, second six of the over. Chahal bowls another slot and Nehal Wadhera punishes. Slog-swept over deep mid
Chahal to Tilak Varma, 1 run, 90.8kph, full on middle and leg, flicked to deep midwicket

Chahal to Tilak Varma, no run, 92.1kph, full toss, Tilak Varma tries to play a premeditated reverse-sweep and is struck on the pad. Appeal for lbw and the dreaded finger goes up quickly. Tilak reviews it though. UltraEdge confirms no bat. Over to ball-tracking and it's missing off. Hit on the full and missing the sticks with the angle. The batters hug as it's a successful review

Chahal to Tilak Varma, SIX, fifty for Tilak Varma, his second this season! A crucial knock from the left-hander with his team under pressure. 89.6kph, airy full ball in the slot, Tilak Varma gets down on one leg to nail the slogsweep. Makes superb contact to dispatch it over deep midwicket
Yuzvendra Chahal [2.0-0-19-1] is back into the attack

Highlights (Overs 7-15) -- 86/1, 9.5 rpo -- Tilak, Nehal lead recovery for MI -- Chahal becomes first bowler to 200 IPL wickets -- He dismisses Nabi for 23 (7.3) -- Tilak, Nehal start steady, then raise tempo -- Ashwin bowls out with 0/31 -- Avesh goes for 19 in his third over (14th over)
Sandeep Sharma to Tilak Varma, 1 run, 115.7kph, Sandeep goes further wide, Tilak slaps the cut to sweeper cover. 11 runs off the over!
Sandeep Sharma to Tilak Varma, FOUR, 122.4kph, clever batting from Tilak Varma! Slow, full and wide off, the batsman sees that coming. Inverses his stance and swings it over short third man
Sandeep Sharma to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, 116.7kph, slower delivery and wide of off on a short of length, Wadhera reaches out and miscues the cut through cover
Sandeep Sharma to Nehal Wadhera, no run, 120.3kph, bumper, Wadhera is early into his pull shot and fails to make contact

Sandeep Sharma to Nehal Wadhera, FOUR, 123.9kph, short outside off, Nehal Wadhera spots it, waits, hops and periscopes it over vacant first slip. Third man was inside the circle and he was a mere spectator
Sandeep Sharma to Tilak Varma, 1 run, 115.8kph, pace off and wide of off, chopped to sweeper cover
Sandeep Sharma [2.0-0-4-2] is back into the attack

Strategic timeout! From 52/4, these two left-handers have done a good job to get their team to this position. Six overs remain, six wickets in hand and MI need a big finish. Sandeep has two overs left while the other two pacers have one apiece. Chahal has two left as well who conceded 13 runs off his 2nd over.
Avesh Khan to Nehal Wadhera, SIX, 135.2kph, harmless short ball and Nehal Wadhera pounces. Sits up nicely for the left-hander who slams the pull over deep square leg. 19 runs off the over!
Avesh Khan to Tilak Varma, 1 run, 140.2kph, full on the stumps, a backing away Tilak Varma drives towards cover
Avesh Khan to Tilak Varma, FOUR, 137.5kph, low full toss and Tilak Varma drives it straight of mid-off. Hetmyer dives but to no avail
Avesh Khan to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, 141.1kph, in-slanting length ball on off from round the wicket, steered to third man
Avesh Khan to Nehal Wadhera, SIX, 121.8kph, slower ball, Wadhera's bottom hand comes off the bat handle but he's made good contact. Clears his front leg to hoist it over long-on for an 86m six
Avesh Khan to Tilak Varma, 1 run, fifty partnership! 137.8kph, Tilak Varma shimmies down the track to slap this back of a length ball. Hits him high on the bat and goes to mid-off
Avesh Khan [2.0-0-24-0] is back into the attack
Ashwin to Nehal Wadhera, 2 runs, 99kph full ball on the pads, Nehal Wadhera plays it with soft hands through mid-wicket and rushes back for the second run. 100 up for MI
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, 1 run, floated outside off, Tilak Varma leans into it and drives it to sweeper cover

Ashwin to Tilak Varma, no run, tossed up well outside off, Tilak Varma is stuck in the crease as he is in two minds whether to go on the front foot or rock back. Looks to chop through point but gets an under-edge besides him
Ashwin to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, fired in again at 101.3kph wide outside off, Nehal Wadhera throws his bat at it and hits it towards sweeper cover
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, 1 run, 97kph low full-toss on off, flicked to long-on to keep things moving
Ashwin to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, fired in at 103.4kph on a length outside off, Nehal Wadhera hits it over covers and it goes to the fielder in the deep on the bounce

Chahal to Tilak Varma, FOUR, this is good batting but not so good bowling! Predictable stuff as it's on a back of a length wide outside off again. Tilak Varma rocks back and cuts it past point. Beats squarish third man with ease as well
Chahal to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, well wide of off once again on a length, Nehal Wadhera flat-bats it to long-off
Chahal to Tilak Varma, 1 run, loopy full ball on off, Tilak Varma drives it on the up to long-off
Chahal to Nehal Wadhera, 2 wides, 92.5kph full ball down leg, Nehal Wadhera looks to lap sweep but misses. It deflects off Samson's pads to the leg-side and the batters take an extra run as well
Chahal to Tilak Varma, 1 run, Tilak Varma is nimble on his feet as he flicks the tossed up ball to deep mid-wicket

Chahal to Tilak Varma, FOUR, a poor delivery and duly punished! A dragdown wide outside off and it's the googly, Tilak Varma rocks back, reaches out to it, and cuts it through covers for a rocketing boundary
Chahal to Tilak Varma, no run, slips in the googy on a back of a length on off, Tilak Varma chops it with the spin to extra cover
Yuzvendra Chahal [1.0-0-6-1] is back into the attack
Ashwin to Nehal Wadhera, FOUR, on the shorter side this time in line of the stumps, Nehal Wadhera lines it up and pulls it over mid-wicket. Beats the fielder in the deep to his right
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, 1 run, turning away a bit from a back of a length on off, Tilak Varma punches it down to long-off
Ashwin to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, on a length on the leg-stump, Nehal Wadhera sweeps it over backward square leg
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, 1 run, Tilak Varma gives himself some room but it's tight bowling by Ashwin. Doesn't let him free his arms and he can only stroke it down to long-off
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, coming in with the arm, Tilak Varma places it with soft hands through mid-wicket and rushes back for the second run
Ashwin to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, fired in on a length on middle at 98.7kph, skids after landing, Nehal Wadhera manages to chop it off his stumps through point
Avesh Khan to Tilak Varma, no run, 131.1kph back of a length ball angling in, Tilak Varma hops and tucks it to mid-wicket
Avesh Khan to Tilak Varma, wide, 121.5kph short ball outside off, it's too high as Tilak Varma has to let it go. Wided for height
Avesh Khan to Tilak Varma, no run, 132.7kph back of a length ball outside off, Tilak Varma cuts it straight to the fielder at point
Avesh Khan to Tilak Varma, no run, 133.9kph good length ball around off, Tilak Varma camps back and pushes it to the off-side

Avesh Khan to Tilak Varma, FOUR, innovative! 138.5kph good length ball outside off, Tilak Varma had shuffled across his stumps as he got low in his stance. Plays the scoop and gets enough on it to get it over short fine
Avesh Khan to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, back of a length ball outside off, Nehal Wadhera opens the face of his bat and guides it to deep backward point

Avesh Khan to Nehal Wadhera, no run, that's a peach! 133.3kph skiddy back of a length ball angling in from round the wicket, Nehal Wadhera is not able to cover the line as the ball straightens a bit and misses the outside edge. There was a stifled appeal for caught behind but there wasn't any wood involved
Avesh Khan [1.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack
Ashwin to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, 95.4kph full ball drifting towards the leg-stump, Nehal Wadhera strides ahead and eases it to long-on
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, 1 run, coming in with the arm and on a back of a length, Tilak Varma knocks it down to long-on
Ashwin to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, quicker through the air and on a length on off, tucked round the corner
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, 1 run, on a back of a length on middle and leg, Tilak Varma makes a bit of room and swipes it to deep mid-wicket

Ashwin to Tilak Varma, SIX, sublime! Tilak Varma uses his feet to the in-drifter, gets to the pitch of it, and lifts it nonchalantly over the bowler's head for a maximum. Hit that one clean as a whistle
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, no run, drifting in towards off, Tilak Varma leans ahead a bit and drives it to extra cover
Chahal to Nehal Wadhera, no run, tossed up on off, Nehal Wadhera lunges and blocks it to covers

Chahal to Nehal Wadhera, FOUR, smartly played! Tossed up outside off and full in length, Nehal Wadhera kneels across on one knee and lap sweeps it through fine leg to find the fence. Picked his spot nicely there
Chahal to Nehal Wadhera, no run, the straighter one on a back of a length on off, Nehal Wadhera hangs back and punches it towards mid-on
Nehal Wadhera, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Time for the strategic break! Just when it was looking like MI were rebuilding a bit after a shoddy start, Chahal has struck to put the breaks once again. MI need a big partnership to gain some momentum
First bowler in IPL to... 50 wickets: RP Singh (12 Apr 2010) 100 wickets: Lasith Malinga (18 May 2013) 150 wickets: Lasith Malinga (6 May 2017) 200 wickets: Yuzvendra Chahal (22 Apr 2024)

Chahal to Nabi, out Caught&Bowled!! Chahal gets his 200th IPL wicket and he is elated! He becomes the first player to get to this milestone. What a moment for the leggie! He gives this one a good amount of air and bowls the conventional leg-spinner on middle and leg, Nabi looks to flick it across but is early into the stroke. Ends up getting a leading edge and Chahal moves a bit to his left to accept it gleefully! Chahal has been a work horse and he has achieved something he will cherish for a lifetime! Nabi c and b Chahal 23(17) [4s-2 6s-1]
Chahal to Nabi, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!
Chahal to Tilak Varma, 1 run, on a length on off at 94.3kph, Tilak Varma hangs back and punches it through mid-wicket
Chahal to Nabi, 1 run, tossed up generously around off, Nabi was shaping for a big shot but adjusts to drive it to sweeper cover
Yuzvendra Chahal, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Ashwin to Nabi, 1 run, floated delivery and full on off, knocked down to long-off for a single
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, 1 run, coming in with the arm and on a back of a length, tucked through wide mid-on
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, no run, loopy full ball on off, Tilak Varma leans into it and drives it to covers
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, wide, back to round the wicket to the left-hander as he fires this one down leg, Tilak Varma looks to glance and misses
Ashwin to Nabi, 1 run, Ashwin switches to over the wicket and bowls a length ball, it turns in, Nabi works it through mid-wicket
A bit of hold up in play
MI batting in Powerplay in IPL 2024 52/2 vs GT 76/2 vs SRH 46/4 vs RR 75/0 vs DC 72/0 vs RCB 63/0 vs CSK 54/1 vs PK 45/3 vs RR I0$
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, 1 run, Tilak Varma uses his feet, converts this one into a full-toss, and whips it to deep mid-wicket
Ashwin to Tilak Varma, no run, Ashwin begins from round the wicket and it comes in with the arm on a length, Tilak Varma pushes it back towards the bowler
Ravichandran Ashwin, right-arm off break, comes into the attack

Powerplay summary -- RR pacers rip apart MI top-order -- Boult and Sandeep utilise early swing superbly -- Rohit dismissed in first over for 6 (0.5) -- RR successfully review to send Kishan packing (1.3) -- Surya falls to Sandeep for 10 (3.1) -- Nabi breaks shackles; Avesh's 1st over goes for 18
Avesh Khan to Tilak Varma, 1 run, 133.7kph back of a length ball outside off, Tilak Varma plays it with soft hands to point for a brisk single. Avesh Khan concedes 18 off his first over
Avesh Khan to Nabi, 1 run, fullish ball swinging in on off, Nabi flicks it to deep mid-wicket

Avesh Khan to Nabi, FOUR, Nabi is growing in confidence! A back of a length ball outside off and some width on offer, Nabi opens his bat-face and places the cut past the left side of point. Sweeper cover has no chance to cut it off
Avesh Khan to Nabi, FOUR, nicely done! A back of a length ball outside off. Nabi camps back and punches it nicely through covers to find the fence
Avesh Khan to Nabi, SIX, shot! A short delivery around off, sits up nicely for Nabi. He stands tall and nails the pull over deep backward square leg for a 68m maximum

Avesh Khan to Nabi, 2 runs, back of a length ball in the off-stump channel, Nabi taps it to the left side of point and calls his partner through. An unnecessary throw from the fielder at the striker's end and the batters take a run off the overthrow
Avesh Khan, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Boult to Nabi, leg byes, 1 run, 131.7kph back of a length ball on leg-stump, Nabi looks to swipe it across but it deflects off his thigh pad towards backward square leg for a leg bye
Boult to Tilak Varma, 1 run, 139.1kph good length ball on off, Tilak Varma camps back and punches it to mid-on for a brisk single
Boult to Nabi, 1 run, back of a length ball outside off, Nabi punches it to sweeper cover to rotate strike

Boult to Tilak Varma, 1 run, 133.6kph length ball just outside off, Tilak Varma hangs back and punches it to the right of point and calls his partner through. The fielder has only one stump to aim at and he misses at the striker's end. Nabi would have been probably safe even if that hit
Boult to Tilak Varma, no run, 138.5kph fuller length ball outside off, Tilak Varma leans ahead a bit and taps it to covers
Boult to Tilak Varma, wide, 137.1kph full ball swinging down leg, wided. Samson had to dive to his right to stop it, it was flying
Boult to Nabi, 1 run, skiddy good length all on off, swinging in, Nabi is stuck to the crease as he pushes at it and ekes an inside edge towards short fine

Sandeep Sharma to Nabi, 1 run, length ball moving in on off, Nabi's feet don't move much as he pushes it through mid-on to get off the mark. A brilliant over from Sandeep Sharma, a wicket and only a run off it
Sandeep Sharma to Nabi, no run, full ball swinging in on middle and leg, Nabi leans ahead and flicks it to the fielder at mid-wicket
Sandeep Sharma to Nabi, no run, probing off-stump channel once again, not giving Nabi any room to play with, He leans ahead and eases it back to Sandeep Sharma
Sandeep Sharma to Nabi, no run, fullish ball swinging in on off, Nabi shuffles a bit and blocks it solidly
Sandeep Sharma to Nabi, no run, fullish ball swinging in nicely, Nabi covers the line to keep it out
Mohammad Nabi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Suryakumar Yadav vs Sandeep Sharma (IPL) 8 innings 32 balls 33 runs Four dismissals Avg 8.25 I0$

Sandeep Sharma to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by Powell!! Sandeep Sharma gets the big fish and he is cock-a-hoop! The ghosts of Wankhede coming back to haunt MI in Jaipur once again. A scrambled seam pitched up ball on middle and off, Suryakumar Yadav shapes to play his signature whip over mid-wicket but is early into the shot. Gets it off the toe-end of the bat as the ball lobs towards mid-on. Powell takes a few steps in front and gets low to take it safely. Suryakumar Yadav c Powell b Sandeep Sharma 10(8) [4s-2]
Sandeep Sharma to Suryakumar Yadav, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Boult to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, 137.4kph good length ball outside off, Suryakumar Yadav swipes it to deep mid-wicket to retain strike
Boult to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, good length ball on off, holds a bit on the surface, Suryakumar Yadav pushes it past the bowler

Boult to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, skiddy back of a length ball in the off-stump channel, Suryakumar Yadav was initially shaping to punch it through covers. But interestingly, he waited for it and opened his bat-face at the last moment to place it past backward point. Was an intelligent shot from a brilliant player
Boult to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, 124.4kph good length ball on off, Suryakumar Yadav hangs back and tucks it to mid-wicket

Boult to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, nicely played! Pitched up outside off and some width on offer, Suryakumar Yadav reaches out to it and drives it past extra cover to find the fence. Was a bit uppish but he found the gap
Boult to Tilak Varma, 1 run, good length ball swinging away from off, Tilak Varma camps back and taps it past backward point

Boult to Tilak Varma, wide, oh, that's nippy! 133kph short ball in line of the stumps, Tilak Varma looks to pull it half-heartedly but misses. The square leg umpire signals a wide for height. RR don't take the review
Most wickets in first over in IPL 26* Trent Boult 25 Bhuvneshwar Kumar 15 Praveen Kumar 13 Sandeep Sharma 12 Deepak Chahar/ Zaheer Khan

Sandeep Sharma to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, good length ball seaming in from outside off, Suryakumar Yadav shuffles a bit and punches it towards mid-on to rotate strike

Sandeep Sharma to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Samson!! RR take a review for a caught behind. Samson was very confident and challenged the call. Was there a nick? Was a fuller length ball that swung away from Ishan Kishan. His feet hardly moved as he poked at it as the ball carried through to the keeper. Time for the replays. Well, well, UltraEdge shows a clear spike when the ball is next to the bat. That's why Samson was so confident when he took it upstairs. MI are once again in some early trouble against RR. Boult to Rohit, out Caught by Samson!! Boult gets the better of Rohit once again! Perhaps it was not a wise call to go for such an expansive shot with the ball swinging appreciably. Fuller in length and moving in, Rohit clears his front leg as he looks to slog it across but only manages to miscue it completely. A lot on hang time on that as Samson gets around it. He gets low to his left and takes it safely. Ideal start for RR. Rohit c Samson b Boult 6(5) [4s-1]
